  "body": "*Type*: Bug\r\n*Summary*: Save button is hidden behind keyboard if type Name for New group chat or New contacts group\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nSave button is shown above the keyboard, as it's in Android\r\n![save in android](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/24173335/f67182e2-0e8b-11e7-87f3-9a188299dd2e.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nSave button is behind a keyboard. So user needs to tap on Return and than on Save\r\n![no save button if keyboard](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/24173413/4bd82b50-0e8c-11e7-923a-b7d6e2f43abc.png)\r\n![save if no keyboard](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/24173427/58104e48-0e8c-11e7-837e-1c5bce78ae07.png)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status and login\r\n- Open Chats\r\n- Tap on plus icon\r\n- Tap on New croup chat\r\n- Select any contact and tap Next\r\n- Type Name of the chat\r\n- Check for Save button\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version:  0.9.4d25\r\n* Operating System: iOS",
